article.headline: UC Davis 60, Ball St. 58
article.story: MUNCIE, Ind. -- Senior forward Dominic Calegari scored 24 points and grabbed seven rebounds, and UC Davis edged ahead in the final minutes to beat Ball State 60-58 Saturday. The Aggies (3-3) trailed 32-28 at halftime and 43-37 with 10:46 to play. But they chipped away, and when Ryan Howley sank two free throws with 4:47 left, the Aggies led 51-50. Ball State never led again. UC Davis managed its late run even with three players fouling out. Jelani Floyd left with 9:36 remaining, Calegari with 2:26 left and Adam Malik 3 seconds later. Joe Harden had 17 points and nine rebounds for UC Davis, and Mark Payne added 11 points and seven assists. Jauwan Scaife led the Cardinals (2-2) with 14 points. Jarrod Jones added 12 and Terrence Watson 11.
